<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Usually erect but occasionally decumbent to ascending cerrado perennial with woody xylopodium, vegetative parts villous with long spreading cobwebby hairs; stems several, erect, herbaceous, 20-30(-50) cm high. Leaves sessile or very shortly petiolate, 1.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.5 cm, ovate to oblong-ovate; base rounded, truncate to subcordate or sagittate; apex acute or (above) apiculate; margin entire; petiole 0(-2) mm. Flowers solitary (rarely paired); peduncles 20-50 mm; bracteoles 3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 mm, linear-lanceolate, finely acuminate; pedicels 5-10 mm; outer sepals 10-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, ovate, acuminate; corolla 3.2-4 cm long, white, unlobed, midpetaline bands pink, long-pilose, terminating in a mucro; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 8-12 mm above base, persistent in fruit; stigmas 3 mm. Capsule glabrous, unusually large, c. 1 cm diameter; seeds smooth. [
<bibRefCitation author="O'Donell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Lilloa" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="421 - 455" refId="B245" refString="O'Donell, CA, 1950. Convolvulaceas americanas nuevas o criticas I. Lilloa 23: 421 - 455" title="Convolvulaceas americanas nuevas o criticas I." volume="23" year="1950">
<normalizedToken originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
1950
</bibRefCitation>
: 430-431, f. 3]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Paraguay (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Krapovickas et al</emphasis>
. 45901, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hassler</emphasis>
9123, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Balansa</emphasis>
1056); Brazil: Parana (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hatschbach</emphasis>
3675, 20011, 30722), Rio Grande do Sul (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Gaudichaud</emphasis>
659). 0-800 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Unique species because of its adaptation to the cerrado biome. The erect habit, xylopodium, woolly, often cobwebby indumentum, subsessile leaves and large corolla all render it distinct from other American species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
